The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Kirkwood had a population of 190. The population density was {{convert|43.6|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Kirkwood was 84.2% [[White Americans|White]], 3.2% [[African Americans|African American]], 3.7% [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 2.6% [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 0.0% [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 1.1% from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 5.3% from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 3.7% of the population.

The Census reported that 72.6% of the population lived in households, 26.8% lived in non-institutionalized group quarters, and 0.5% were institutionalized.

There were 81 households, out of which 8.6% included children under the age of 18, 13.6% were married-couple households, 11.1% were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 18.5% had a female householder with no partner present, and 56.8% had a male householder with no partner present. 56.8% of households were one person, and 7.4% were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 1.7. There were 22 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (27.2% of all households).

The age distribution was 5.8% under the age of 18, 11.1% aged 18 to 24, 33.2% aged 25 to 44, 34.2% aged 45 to 64, and 15.8% who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 45.0{{nbsp}}years. There were 121 males and 69 females.

There were 659 housing units at an average density of {{convert|151.2|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 81 (12.3%) were occupied. Of these, 32.1% were owner-occupied, and 67.9% were occupied by renters.<ref>{{cite web |title=Kirkwood CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0638646 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=March 24, 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Kirkwood CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0638646 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=March 24, 2025}}</ref>

